        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 20 at 6:49PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 648 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cassopolis, or 12 miles east of Dowagiac, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Marcellus, Penn, Vandalia, Jones, Donnell Lake, and Wakelee.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
